The paper discusses coalition-proof mechanisms in auctions, which falls under the field of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces concepts related to optimization and profit maximization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the application of these concepts to electricity markets, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
